              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Nergal</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/19/2003&nbsp;: 2:03:01 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> AAs and Focus effects DO stack.<br /><br />Specialization is a 2.5% mana savings per 50 points. So 10% (200) for whatever you specilized in (alteration for most of us), and 2.5% (50) for the others.<br /><br />Spell Casting Mastery is, by level, 2%, 5%, and 10% additional mana savings. (now 20% for what you specialized in and 12.5% for the others).<br /><br />Focus effects like Mana Preservation and Affcliction Efficiency stack on top of that, at a flat rate.  So assuming you use an Affliction Efficiency item (25% mana saving) you're now up to 45% in you specializtion, and 37.5% in non-specialized areas (for DoTs only).<br /></span></font></td>
              </tr>
